<span id="freeTextContainer13617623076228355943">Absolute, complete, TRASH! <br/><br/>I have ranted extensively about this book at <a href='http://www.solomonsays.in/items/13' rel='nofollow noopener'>SolomonSays</a>, but still not over it - so here goes again.<br/><br/>This is not a philosophy book. The discipline of philosophy is the discipline of asking questions and finding out answers. On the contrary, the formula of The Consolations of philosophy is quite the opposite. The author will find out the answers for your common problems, and dish them out. On top of that, his answers are not his own. He just plucked out six great thinke</span>
  <span id="freeText13617623076228355943" style="display:none">Absolute, complete, TRASH! <br /><br />I have ranted extensively about this book at <a href="http://www.solomonsays.in/items/13" rel="nofollow noopener">SolomonSays</a>, but still not over it - so here goes again.<br /><br />This is not a philosophy book. The discipline of philosophy is the discipline of asking questions and finding out answers. On the contrary, the formula of The Consolations of philosophy is quite the opposite. The author will find out the answers for your common problems, and dish them out. On top of that, his answers are not his own. He just plucked out six great thinkers, dumbed down their ideas, and had them published.<br /><br />It's like going to a doctor who prescribes only generic drugs, and that too after asking his old uncle who used to be a great doctor. <br /><br /></span>
